This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with predicting mobility in wireless Ad Hoc networks. Additionally, the use of neural networks suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on improving routing and reducing connection interruptions could also place it in the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Information Theory (cs.IT).
